Two S&Ls Added to Program

   RTC closed the year by taking over two small thrifts: the $70.9 million-
asset Columbia FSA, Webster, Tex., and the $27.5 million-asset Silver SA
FA, Silver City, N.M.
   During 1989 the agency resolved 37 institutions, as shown in the
breakdown below. Another 11 were advertised for sale in November, and those
transactions should be completed shortly.



